The paper proposes a system for querying knowledge graphs, which involves database-related tasks such as query processing and ranking. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DB (Databases). The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques for finding and ranking approximate answer tuples, making cs.IR a likely sub-category as well. The use of machine learning and natural language processing (NLP) techniques for query processing and ranking suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of deep learning (DL) and graph-based algorithms, making cs.DL and cs.LG (Machine Learning and Learning) possible sub-categories as well.
